  "prompt": "How long does it take to grow hair after a person has shaved his/her head? What's the regular growth rate?",
  "response": "The rate at which hair grows can vary from person to person, but on average, human hair grows about half an inch (1.25 cm) per month. This means in a year, hair can grow approximately 6 inches (15 cm). These growth rates can be influenced by various factors such as genetics, age, health, diet, and hair care practices.\n\nAfter shaving your head, you might notice some stubble within a few days. Within a month, you can typically expect about half an inch of hair growth. Keep in mind that individual factors can cause variations in these estimates.",
